        "timestamp": "2018-09-21 14:41:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI can check with the aai team if I can make the name more generic so that other repos can use it. I will change the name of the job and let you know about it soon",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8f732a3512a76aba55c3ef85321a0f4b9368f5d9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-21 22:26:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nRavi, can you please use \"{project-name}-{stream}-aai-docker-java-daily\" template for the moment please?\n\nI noticed that changing the name will confuse AAI in quite a lot of repos and seems like other projects like CLI and VNFSDK are already using it too which will confuse them too. \n\nI know it looks ugly, but you can set a comment in your yaml explaining that even though the name is AAI, there is no AAI code involved. Seems like teams are using this template knowing that. \n\nAlso, This will all be adjusted once we move to the generic docker jobs",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
